# Universal Modals

Use the shared stack-based modal system via `useModal()`. Do not build one-off Dialog/AlertDialog wiring for confirms, blocking notifications, or form dialogs when this fits.

## Layout

| Concern | Path |
|---------|------|
| Types | `src/components/shared/modals/types.ts` |
| Provider / reducer | `src/components/shared/modals/modal-context.tsx` |
| Public hook | `src/components/shared/modals/use-modal.ts` |
| Renderers + dirty guard | `src/components/shared/modals/modal-root.tsx` |
| App mount | `ModalProvider` + `ModalRoot` in `src/components/shared/layout/app-providers.tsx` |

## Choosing an API

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Must-decide yes/no | `confirm({ title, message, variant? })` → `Promise<boolean>` |
| Blocking acknowledge | `notify({ variant, title, message })` |
| Form in a dialog | `openModal({ type: "form", component, title?, size? })` |
| Transient feedback | Toast — not this system |
| Auth / permission from `useError().run()` | Already routed to `notify` — do not duplicate |

## Form modal pattern

Capture the id returned by `openModal` (sync) so content can report dirty and close on submit:

```tsx
// ✅ form modal + dirty bridge
let formId = ""
formId = openModal({
  type: "form",
  title: "New User",
  size: "lg",
  component: (
    <UserForm
      onDirtyChange={(isDirty) => setDirty(formId, isDirty)}
      onSubmit={async (values) => {
        await save(values)
        closeModal(formId)
      }}
    />
  ),
})
```

- Callers never invent `id` or pass `isDirty` in the config.
- Dirty close is handled by the modal system (discard confirm stacks on top).
- Successful submit closes via `closeModal(formId)` — no discard prompt.

## List-page CRUD

Wire Create/Edit/Delete on list pages via `DynamicTable` `toolbarActions` / `rowActions` + this modal API. Submit with `useError().run()` + `applyServerErrors`; success → toast + `closeModal` + reload. Delete → `confirm({ variant: "destructive" })`. Gate write UI with `hasPermission` from `@/features/auth/permissions`. See `.docs/components/modals.md` § List-page CRUD.

## Constraints

- Named exports only; no `any`.
- Modal package must **not** import `DynamicForm`, `FieldDef`, or feature forms — `component` is opaque `ReactNode`.
- Compose modals + forms only at the call site (use form `onDirtyChange`).
- No auto-dismiss / timeouts (toasts own that).
- Prefer `useModal` over `useModalContext` in feature/app code.
- Use shadcn Dialog / AlertDialog as-is; do not reimplement portal/overlay/focus-trap.

See `.docs/components/modals.md` for the full human guide.
